For the next iteration, 
\begin_inset Formula $i=2$
\end_inset

, say we again yield 
\begin_inset Formula $c=-1$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\psi\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 is also unchanged, the assignment remains invariant.
 For the final step, we choose to measure 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{p}=\hat{A}_{23}(=\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y})$
\end_inset

, to proceed with sequentially measuring 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{C}_{3}$
\end_inset

.
 To simplify calculations, we note 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left|00\right\rangle =\frac{(\left|\tilde{+}\tilde{-}\right\rangle +\left|\tilde{-}\tilde{+}\right\rangle )/\sqrt{2}+(\left|\tilde{+}\tilde{+}\right\rangle +\left|\tilde{-}\tilde{-}\right\rangle )/\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{2}},
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\tilde{\pm}\right\rangle =\left|0\right\rangle \pm i\left|1\right\rangle $
